      "generation_context": "1st-gen (X761), introduced 2016; 2021 mid-cycle refresh (current shape, interior redesign, Pivi Pro infotainment); 2026 is the final model year — last F-PACE was built at Solihull on December 19, 2025, also marking the end of Jaguar ICE production",
      "msrp_range": {
        "low": 57000,
        "high": 92400
      },
      "model_summary": "The F-PACE is Jaguar's compact luxury SUV and the final ICE Jaguar nameplate sold new in the US. The MY26 lineup is a three-trim final run while the brand transitions to an EV-only repositioning: P250 R-Dynamic S (turbo I4), P400 R-Dynamic S (mild-hybrid inline-six), and SVR 575 Edition (supercharged V8). All trims share the EVA 2.0 architecture, standard AWD, 8-speed automatic, an 11.4-inch Pivi Pro infotainment screen, and Jaguar EliteCare warranty.",
      "reliability": {
        "jd_power_vds_score": null,
        "jd_power_vds_year": null,
        "consumer_reports_predicted_reliability": null,
        "summary": "Jaguar does not appear in the published JD Power 2026 VDS premium-brand rankings released February 2026 (Lexus 151 PP100, Cadillac 175 PP100, Porsche 182 PP100 led the segment; premium-segment average 217 PP100), reflecting Jaguar's low US sales volume. The 2023 VDS recorded Jaguar at 229 PP100 — below the premium-segment average and toward the bottom of the rankings. Consumer Reports also has insufficient survey sample to publish a numeric predicted-reliability score and notes only that it 'expects the 2025 F-Pace to be less reliable than other new cars' based on brand history. The F-PACE has had recalls in MY24 for an oil filter housing crack and Near Field Sensing Module overheating.",
        "confidence": "low",
