          "notes": "Base of the SVR (5.0L V8 supercharged, ICE) performance line — separate powertrain line per project convention for high-output specialty performance variants (analogous to BMW M50, AMG, etc.). Jaguar SVO markets it as a dedicated Special Vehicle Operations product with its own page on jaguar.com (dedicated bodywork, suspension, exhaust, interior, EVA 2.0 architecture). Singleton trim_family per sole-trim atomic rule (is_base_trim:true, delta_from_base:null). 575 PS = 567 hp SAE. NHTSA and IIHS have not crash-tested the SVR (low-volume specialty performance variant) — null per spec convention. The 5.0L AJ133 supercharged V8 was the final V8 engine in Jaguar production; the last F-PACE SVR rolled off Solihull December 19, 2025. Some dealers list a parallel 'SVR 575 Final Edition' at $95,000 MSRP for late-build units (a $2,600 premium); the Jaguar US consumer site shows only 'SVR 575 Edition' as the trim name, so this catalog records only the manufacturer-listed SVR 575 Edition. The Jaguar Australia-exclusive 'SVR 575 Ultimate Edition' (60 units) is not sold in the US."
