      "researched_at": "2026-05-13",
      "notes": "Final model year of the F-PACE — last F-PACE was built at JLR Solihull on December 19, 2025, marking the end of Jaguar ICE production worldwide. The MY26 US lineup is a three-trim catalog (P250 R-Dynamic S, P400 R-Dynamic S, SVR 575 Edition); all three are treated as singleton trim_families and is_base_trim:true with delta_from_base:null per the sole-trim atomic rule and Land Rover precedent for three distinct powertrain lines (P250 I4 turbo, P400 I6 MHEV, SVR V8 supercharged — all classified as powertrain.type='ice' per project convention that 48V MHEV is ICE). The 'SVR 575 Final Edition' label seen at $95,000 on some dealer pages and on Edmunds is not a separately-listed manufacturer trim on jaguar.com/en-us — it appears to be a dealer/aggregator label for late-allocation SVR 575 Edition units and was not treated as a fourth trim here. The 90th Anniversary Edition referenced in Jaguar's May 2024 press release is a European option pack with diesel MHEV and PHEV powertrains and was not offered in the US. Dimensions and weights sourced from a combination of Jaguar Jordan 25MY spec sheet (mirroring JLR global) and the iSeeCars aggregated spec database since the US jaguar.com Specifications page returns 'information unavailable' as of the research date. All three trims are AWD with the 8-speed ZF automatic. Jaguar's brand identity is mid-transition to EV-only ('Copy Nothing. The New Era Begins'); the Type 01 GT EV is targeted to debut in summer 2026 with initial deliveries to follow, but as of 2026-05-13 the Type 01 is not yet on sale and the F-PACE is the only Jaguar nameplate currently bookable on jaguar.com/en-us. XE, XF, F-TYPE production ended mid-2024; E-PACE and I-PACE production ended December 2024 — none are 2026 model-year vehicles per EPA fueleconomy.gov."
